HEADWORD: Europium
<hw>Eu*ro"pi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.;
<ets>Europe</ets> + <ets>-ium</ets>, as in alumin<ets>ium</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A metallic element of the rare-earth group
(Lanthanide series), discovered spectroscopically by
<persfn>Demarcay</persfn> in 1896. Symbol, <it>Eu</it>; atomic number
63; at. wt., 151.965 (C=12.011); valence = +2 or +3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

